[[File:Leech dark alliance.jpg|thumb|''Leeches feeding on a [[humanoid]] brain.''|395x395px]]
Leeches were highly vulnerable to [[salt]] and the application of sufficient amounts could kill them.

Like many species of invertebrate, leeches had a set of [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simple_eye_in_invertebrates ocelli] in place of normal eyes. These were a group of light receptive cells that could register changes in light intensity, though not actual images. Because of this, giant leeches often reacted to changes in nearby light.{{Cite dragon/123/Ecology of the Giant Leech|52}}
